cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and summarization. Additionally, the use of attention mechanisms and neural networks further supports this categorization. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the development of a neural summarization model. The use of graph representations suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
